Apprs: CO: SRN, Rpr: Kasten, Clerk: Evenson. ADA: Michael Edward Nieskes DF ATTY: John A. Kucinski DF:  Billie Jo Haynes appeared. Case called at 3:28. ADA Nieskes updates the court. Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads NC to amended charge of misdemeanor theft Ct 1, 2, 3  in15CF338. DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of amended Ct 1,2,3 in 15CF338. On motion of the State without objection, Crt dismisses Ct 4,5 and 6 in 15CF338. Sentencing arguments. Crt orders: Sentence W/H
Ct. 1
- 2 years probation with conditions:
- restitution joint and several to be set after restitution hearing. 
- restitution joint and several to be set after restitution hearing. 
- Costs of 243.00 
- Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge.
- It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Wayne B., Jennifer L and the storage units in Glenwood City, WI.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, social media including but not limited to texting, Facebook, Twitter, contact through the mail, and/or through a third person. 

Ct. 2
2 years probation concurrent to Ct. 1 with same conditions as Ct. 1
Probation is concurrent without prejudice to consecutive sentencing in the event of Probation revocation.
- Costs of 243.00 
- Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge.

Ct. 3
2 years probation concurrent to Ct. 1 and 2 with same conditions as Ct. 1
Probation is concurrent without prejudice to consecutive sentencing in the event of Probation revocation.
- Costs of 243.00
